{"id":1820,"date":"2021-11-03T03:57:39","date_gmt":"2021-11-03T03:57:39","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/?p=1820"},"modified":"2021-12-23T17:07:56","modified_gmt":"2021-12-23T17:07:56","slug":"menu-settings","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/2021\/11\/03\/menu-settings\/","title":{"rendered":"Menu Settings"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>To make the most of your menus, you should be familiar with the various settings and options that come with it. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These are a mixture of WordPress core menu settings, and UDesign added settings.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"alert alert-info alert-light mt-4 mb-4\"><strong>Note:<\/strong> There are 2 levels of menu items, the First Level menu items and the Sub-level menu items below the First Level menu item. Colored settings are only available for only First Level menu.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Navigation Label:<\/strong> Input menu label.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>No Link:<\/strong> If checked, menu item won&#8217;t lead to your url on click.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong class=\"text-primary\">Megamenu<\/strong>: If checked, Sub-level menu items would be displayed as megamenu type.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong class=\"text-primary\">Megamenu Width:<\/strong> Input megamenu width in pixels.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong class=\"text-primary\">Megamenu Position:<\/strong> Display megamenu in left, center or right of First Level menu.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Prefix Icon Class:<\/strong> Input icon class to show before menu label starts.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Add Label:<\/strong> Select a label to show on top right of menu item. You could add menu labels in &nbsp;<code class=\"code-grey\">UDesign &gt; Theme Options &gt; Menus &gt; Menu Labels<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>CSS Classes (optional)<\/strong>: Input custom class to current menu item.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Use Block:<\/strong> Select a UDesign Block template to display. This option works only for Sub-level menu items under not checked megamenu setting.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>To make the most of your menus, you should be familiar with the various settings and options that come with it. These are a mixture of WordPress core menu settings, and UDesign added settings. Note: There are 2 levels of menu items, the First Level menu items and the Sub-level menu items below the First [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[9],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1820"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1820"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1820\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2826,"href":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1820\/revisions\/2826"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1820"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=1820"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=1820"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel